        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The following procedure shows how to create a <ph id="ph1">`CTime`</ph> object and initialize it with the current time.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>To get the current time</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Allocate a <ph id="ph1">`CTime`</ph> object, as follows:</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>NVC_ATLMFC_Utilities#171</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Uninitialized <ph id="ph1">`CTime`</ph> objects are not initialized to a valid time.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Call the <ph id="ph1">`CTime::GetCurrentTime`</ph> function to get the current time from the operating system.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This function returns a <ph id="ph1">`CTime`</ph> object that can be used to set the value of <ph id="ph2">`CTime`</ph>, as follows:</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>NVC_ATLMFC_Utilities#172</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Since <ph id="ph1">`GetCurrentTime`</ph> is a static member function from the <ph id="ph2">`CTime`</ph> class, you must qualify its name with the name of the class and the scope resolution operator (<ph id="ph3">`::`</ph>), <ph id="ph4">`CTime::GetCurrentTime()`</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
